00052 static struct lu_buf *seq_store_buf(struct seq_thread_info *info)
00053 {
00054         struct lu_buf *buf;
00055 
00056         buf = &info->sti_buf;
00057         buf->lb_buf = &info->sti_space;
00058         buf->lb_len = sizeof(info->sti_space);
00059         return buf;
00060 }

00062 struct seq_update_callback {
00063         struct dt_txn_commit_cb suc_cb;
00064         struct lu_server_seq   *suc_seq;
00065 };
00066 
00067 void seq_update_cb(struct lu_env *env, struct thandle *th,
00068                    struct dt_txn_commit_cb *cb, int err)
00069 {
00070         struct seq_update_callback *ccb;
00071 
00072         ccb = container_of0(cb, struct seq_update_callback, suc_cb);
00073 
00074         LASSERT(ccb->suc_seq != NULL);
00075 
00076         ccb->suc_seq->lss_need_sync = 0;
00077         OBD_FREE_PTR(ccb);
00078 }
00079 
00080 int seq_update_cb_add(struct thandle *th, struct lu_server_seq *seq)
00081 {
00082         struct seq_update_callback *ccb;
00083         struct dt_txn_commit_cb    *dcb;
00084         int                        rc;
00085 
00086         OBD_ALLOC_PTR(ccb);
00087         if (ccb == NULL)
00088                 return -ENOMEM;
00089 
00090         ccb->suc_seq       = seq;
00091         seq->lss_need_sync = 1;
00092 
00093         dcb            = &ccb->suc_cb;
00094         dcb->dcb_func  = seq_update_cb;
00095         INIT_LIST_HEAD(&dcb->dcb_linkage);
00096         strlcpy(dcb->dcb_name, "seq_update_cb", sizeof(dcb->dcb_name));
00097 
00098         rc = dt_trans_cb_add(th, dcb);
00099         if (rc)
00100                 OBD_FREE_PTR(ccb);
00101         return rc;
00102 }

00104 /* This function implies that caller takes care about locking. */
00105 int seq_store_update(const struct lu_env *env, struct lu_server_seq *seq,
00106                      struct lu_seq_range *out, int sync)
00107 {
00108         struct dt_device *dt_dev = lu2dt_dev(seq->lss_obj->do_lu.lo_dev);
00109         struct seq_thread_info *info;
00110         struct thandle *th;
00111         loff_t pos = 0;
00112         int rc;
00113 
00114         info = lu_context_key_get(&env->le_ctx, &seq_thread_key);
00115         LASSERT(info != NULL);
00116 
00117         th = dt_trans_create(env, dt_dev);
00118         if (IS_ERR(th))
00119                 RETURN(PTR_ERR(th));
00120 
00121         /* Store ranges in le format. */
00122         range_cpu_to_le(&info->sti_space, &seq->lss_space);
00123 
00124         rc = dt_declare_record_write(env, seq->lss_obj,
00125                                      seq_store_buf(info), 0, th);
00126         if (rc)
00127                 GOTO(exit, rc);
00128 
00129         if (out != NULL) {
00130                 rc = fld_declare_server_create(env,
00131                                                seq->lss_site->ss_server_fld,
00132                                                out, th);
00133                 if (rc)
00134                         GOTO(exit, rc);
00135         }
00136 
00137         rc = dt_trans_start_local(env, dt_dev, th);
00138         if (rc)
00139                 GOTO(exit, rc);
00140 
00141         rc = dt_record_write(env, seq->lss_obj, seq_store_buf(info), &pos, th);
00142         if (rc) {
00143                 CERROR("%s: Can't write space data, rc %d\n",
00144                        seq->lss_name, rc);
00145                 GOTO(exit, rc);
00146         } else if (out != NULL) {
00147                 rc = fld_server_create(env, seq->lss_site->ss_server_fld, out,
00148                                        th);
00149                 if (rc) {
00150                         CERROR("%s: Can't Update fld database, rc %d\n",
00151                                 seq->lss_name, rc);
00152                         GOTO(exit, rc);
00153                 }
00154         }
00155         /* next sequence update will need sync until this update is committed
00156          * in case of sync operation this is not needed obviously */
00157         if (!sync)
00158                 /* if callback can't be added then sync always */
00159                 sync = !!seq_update_cb_add(th, seq);
00160 
00161         th->th_sync |= sync;
00162 exit:
00163         dt_trans_stop(env, dt_dev, th);
00164         return rc;
00165 }

00167 /*
00168  * This function implies that caller takes care about locking or locking is not
00169  * needed (init time).
00170  */
00171 int seq_store_read(struct lu_server_seq *seq,
00172                    const struct lu_env *env)
00173 {
00174         struct seq_thread_info *info;
00175         loff_t pos = 0;
00176         int rc;
00177         ENTRY;
00178 
00179         info = lu_context_key_get(&env->le_ctx, &seq_thread_key);
00180         LASSERT(info != NULL);
00181 
00182         rc = dt_read(env, seq->lss_obj, seq_store_buf(info), &pos);
00183 
00184         if (rc == sizeof(info->sti_space)) {
00185                 range_le_to_cpu(&seq->lss_space, &info->sti_space);
00186                 CDEBUG(D_INFO, "%s: Space - "DRANGE"\n",
00187                        seq->lss_name, PRANGE(&seq->lss_space));
00188                 rc = 0;
00189         } else if (rc == 0) {
00190                 rc = -ENODATA;
00191         } else if (rc > 0) {
00192                 CERROR("%s: Read only %d bytes of %d\n", seq->lss_name,
00193                        rc, (int)sizeof(info->sti_space));
00194                 rc = -EIO;
00195         }
00196 
00197         RETURN(rc);
00198 }

00200 int seq_store_init(struct lu_server_seq *seq,
00201                    const struct lu_env *env,
00202                    struct dt_device *dt)
00203 {
00204         struct dt_object *dt_obj;
00205         struct lu_fid fid;
00206         struct lu_attr attr;
00207         struct dt_object_format dof;
00208         const char *name;
00209         int rc;
00210         ENTRY;
00211 
00212         name = seq->lss_type == LUSTRE_SEQ_SERVER ?
00213                 LUSTRE_SEQ_SRV_NAME : LUSTRE_SEQ_CTL_NAME;
00214 
00215         if (seq->lss_type == LUSTRE_SEQ_SERVER)
00216                 lu_local_obj_fid(&fid, FID_SEQ_SRV_OID);
00217         else
00218                 lu_local_obj_fid(&fid, FID_SEQ_CTL_OID);
00219 
00220         memset(&attr, 0, sizeof(attr));
00221         attr.la_valid = LA_MODE;
00222         attr.la_mode = S_IFREG | 0666;
00223         dof.dof_type = DFT_REGULAR;
00224 
00225         dt_obj = dt_find_or_create(env, dt, &fid, &dof, &attr);
00226         if (!IS_ERR(dt_obj)) {
00227                 seq->lss_obj = dt_obj;
00228                 rc = 0;
00229         } else {
00230                 CERROR("%s: Can't find \"%s\" obj %d\n",
00231                        seq->lss_name, name, (int)PTR_ERR(dt_obj));
00232                 rc = PTR_ERR(dt_obj);
00233         }
00234 
00235         RETURN(rc);
00236 }

00238 void seq_store_fini(struct lu_server_seq *seq,
00239                     const struct lu_env *env)
00240 {
00241         ENTRY;
00242 
00243         if (seq->lss_obj != NULL) {
00244                 if (!IS_ERR(seq->lss_obj))
00245                         lu_object_put(env, &seq->lss_obj->do_lu);
00246                 seq->lss_obj = NULL;
00247         }
00248 
00249         EXIT;
00250 }
